          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">On Tuesday afternoo=
n, the ever-disciplined, often soft-spoken, and normally besuited veteran p=
olitico and newsman <b>George Stephanopoulos</b> was marauding up Fifth Ave=
nue in a t-shirt and gym shorts when he was accosted by a passerby, who sou=
ght to extemporaneously follow up on the anchor=E2=80=99s recent newsmaking=
 interview with embattled president <b>Joe Biden</b>. So, this passerby wan=
ted to know, did <i>George </i>think the president should step down? =E2=80=
=9CI don=E2=80=99t think he can serve four more years,=E2=80=9D Stephanopou=
los casually responded. In a matter of minutes, the secretly taped footage =
was furnished to TMZ.<br/><br/>In light of the national fervor over Biden=
=E2=80=99s disastrous debate performance, two weeks ago, Stephanopoulos=E2=
=80=99s gaffe struck a nerve. Through a spokesperson, he told me he =E2=80=
=9Cshouldn=E2=80=99t have=E2=80=9D responded to his interlocutor.
Meanwhile, his network distanced itself from what it stressed was their $20=
 million dollar-a-year anchor=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cown point of view.=E2=80=
=9D But it was obvious to <i>everyone </i>that George had meant what he=E2=
=80=99d said and that it was indeed <i>yet another</i> meaningful vote of n=
o confidence in the president=E2=80=94not just from someone who had recentl=
y sat down with him in person, but from a 30-year veteran journalist <i>and=
 </i>former Democratic White House press secretary who has deep respect for=
 the office and the institution.<br/><br/>Indeed, in phone calls and text m=
essages on Tuesday night, some of Stephanopoulos=E2=80=99s friends and long=
time colleagues wondered whether this was a gaffe or simply his subconsciou=
s attempt to reckon with his frustrations as a concerned American instituti=
onalist? =E2=80=9CThis moment truly, deeply upsets him,=E2=80=9D one longti=
me colleague told me. =E2=80=9C<b>Trump</b> is a clear and present danger, =
and Biden is manifestly in decline and unfit for another four years.
Which is why the inner agony came out to a random person on the street. He =
couldn=E2=80=99t contain it. It matters too much to him.=E2=80=9D<br/></td>
         </tr>
